Ordered take out last night and it was my first visit here. The place was packed on a Friday night and I'm pretty sure I took the last parking spot in this very crowded stripmall. I've never had Korean food before so I went with the most popular yelp item reviewed... the meat jun

From the first bite, I was in love. There's this burst of flavor that reminds me of food I've had in Hawaii (go figure). I know something is good when I can't stop thinking about how good it was and when I can get back. Thank goodness I live close by  so Island Style will be one of my new hot spots. I'm definitely looking forward to the eating in experience.

I have to thank yelpers for finding this as I don't think I honestly would have ever tried it on my own.